Add one sachet of OPTIFAST® VLCD™ to 200-250mL of cold or warm water. Stir, blend or shake to dissolve. Do not use boiling water. All prepared products should be tightly covered and consumed within 6 hours at room temperature or within 24 hours if refrigerated. Note: Do not change proportions. Follow preparation instructions. Discard any unfinished product that has been heated.
Very Low Energy Diet: For Intensive Level of the program, replace all meals with three OPTIFAST® VLCD™ products per day. Additionally, consume a minimum of two litres of calorie-free fluid and at least two cups of low starch vegetables with one teaspoon of vegetable oil per day. A program of regular light exercise enhances wellbeing and the likelihood of success. One serve of OPTIFAST® VLCD™ Shake can be replaced with one serve of any other product in the OPTIFAST® VLCD™ range (Desserts, Soups, Bars).

name: RESOURCE® ThickenUp® 125g
description:
Nestlé Health Science RESOURCE® ThickenUp® Clear is the clear solution for dysphagia.  Our exclusive patented xanthan gum formulation offers a clear solution for patients and clinicians. Resource® ThickenUp® Clear is a food for special medical purposes for the dietary management of people with swallowing difficulties. Instant Food and Drink Thickener. Transparent, tasteless, odourless and lump-free. Easy to mix and easy to measure. Rapid thickening and stabilisation. Innovative Technology: Patented process and exclusive Xanthan-gum blend. Its proven amylase resistance ensures stable consistency during the entire swallowing process.  Improves Compliance: Does not affect colour, taste and odour of hot or cold liquids or foods.

name: OPTIFAST® VLCD™ Soup 53g Sachet
description:
The easy to prepare Soup products are part of the OPTIFAST® VLCD™ range and a perfect option for a savoury, hot and satisfying meal that can be enjoyed at any time of the day.  The Soups come in 3 delicious flavours Chicken, Tomato Country Style and Vegetable.
They are part of a nutritionally complete Program, that is high in protein, is a source of fibre.
OPTIFAST® VLCD™ should be taken under the supervision of a healthcare professional.
Very Low Energy Diet. Take an additional two litres of calorie-Free fluid each day. Unsuitable for use by Pregnant or Lactating Women, Infants, children, Adolescents or People Older than 65 years of age.

Usage:
For best results, add one sachet of OPTIFAST® VLCD™ to 200-250mL of cold water in a shaker.  Shake vigorously.  Pour soup into a microwaveable bowl or cup.  Microwave on high for 20 seconds then stir contents.  Keep heating in 20 second intervals, stirring after each time, until desired temperature is reached.  Do Not Boil.
Alternatively, add one sachet to 200-250ml cold water, stir vigorously with a whisk, gently heat on the stove whilst stirring until desired temperature is reached. Do Not Boil.
All prepared products should be tightly covered and consumed within 6 hours at room temperature or within 24 hours if refrigerated.
Note: Do not change proportions. Follow preparation instructions. Discard any unfinished product that has been heated.
Very Low Energy Diet: For Intensive Level of the program, replace all meals with three OPTIFAST® VLCD™ products per day. Additionally, consume a minimum of two litres of calorie-free fluid and at least two cups of low starch vegetables with one teaspoon of vegetable oil per day. A program of regular light exercise enhances wellbeing and the likelihood of success. One serve of OPTIFAST® VLCD™ Soup can be replaced with one serve of any other product in the OPTIFAST® VLCD™ range (Desserts, Shakes, Bars).

Instructions1. Wash hands. 2. Measure 210ml clean water (room temperature to maintain probiotic activity) and pour into a clean container.3. Measure 55g or 7 scoops of powder using the scoop (1 x scoop of Kid Essentials® = approx. 8g) provided in the tin. 4. Add the powder to the water and immediately stir until thoroughly mixed.5. Use only enclosed scoop
Dosage may vary depending on your child's nutrition requirements. For advice on the correct dosage for your child always contact your health professional.
All prepared products should be tightly covered and consumed within 6 hours at room temperature or within 24 hours if refrigerated.
Store in a cool dry place and use within 4 weeks after opening
Note: Do not change proportions.  Follow feeding instructions.

name: SUSTAGEN® OPTIMUM 800g
description:
Nestlé Health ScienceSUSTAGEN® OPTIMUM™ is a balanced oral supplement that contains pre and probiotics, antioxidant vitamins C &amp; E, and high quality protein providing 1.06 kcal/mL per suggested serving. It is also low in lactose.
SUSTAGEN® OPTIMUM™ tastes great and provides complete nutrition so you can use it as a supplement when you are unable to meet your nutrient requirements through dietary intake alone. This could be due to poor appetite or illness , particularly if you have been taking antibiotics. It contains probiotics and dietary fibres (prebiotics) to support digestive function and high quality protein to help maintain muscle mass. It also contains 27 essential vitamins and minerals , including dietary antioxidant vitamins C &amp; E and copper, iron, selenium and zinc to support immune function. SUSTAGEN® OPTIMUM™ is also low in lactose and has a low GI. For more information visit www.sustagen.com.au

Contains Milk and Soy.

name: SUSTAGEN® Diabetic Ready to Drink 237ml
description:
Nestlé Health Science SUSTAGEN® Diabetic is a lower carbohydrate** oral supplement specifically formulated for people with diabetes. It is high in fibre and has a low GI ,  and provides 1.0kcal/mL. If you have diabetes and haven't been eating well ,   you may benefit from SUSTAGEN® Diabetic. It provides energy ,  high quality protein ,  fibre and 27 vitamins and minerals. It is high in fibre ,  lower in carbohydrate** and has a low Glycemic Index to help avoid large fluctuations in blood glucose levels. **Compared to SUSTAGEN Hospital Formula on a per serve basis. SUSTAGEN® Diabetic is specifically formulated for people with diabetes who cannot meet their nutritional needs through diet modification alone. Suitable as a sole source of nutrition. Use under medical supervision. For more information visit www.sustagen.com.au.

Mix 3 level scoops* with 200ml water or milk (depending on taste). Use enclosed scoop.  * 1 x scoop of SUSTAGEN® = 20g.  Stir before serving.  Great chilled or served warm.
All prepared products should be tightly covered and consumed within 6 hours at room temperature or within 24 hours if refrigerated.
Note: Do not change proportions.  Follow feeding instructions.
Keep the can tightly closed.  Store in a cool dry place.

description:

name: ISOSOURCE® 2.0 1000mL
description:
Isosource® 2.0 is an energy dense liquid formula for increased energy requirements and restricted fluid volume. Suitable for tube feed and provides 2.0 kcal/ml.
Specifically formulated for the dietary management of malnutrition and other medical conditions with increased nutritional needs that cannot be met through diet modification alone.
Must be used under medical supervision. Suitable for use as a sole source of nutrition.
Recommended Daily Intake: Meets 100% of RDI for 24 key micronutrients in 800ml.
ingredients: Neutral:  Water, Corn Syrup, Milk Proteins(Sodium Caseinate, Calcium Caseinate), Medium Chain Tryglyceride, Vegetable Oil (Low Erucic Acid Rapessed), Soy Protein Isolate, Maltodextrin (Corn), Minerals (Sodium Citrate, Calcium Phosphate, Potassium Chloride, Calcium Citrate, Magnesium Phosphate, Potassium Citrate, Magnesium Oxide, Zinc Sulphate, Ferrous Sulphate, Manganese Sulphate, Copper Sulphate, Chromium Chloride, PotassiumIodide, Sodium Molybdate, Sodium Selenate), Emulsifier (Soy Lecithin), Vitamins (Sodium Ascorbate, Alpha-Tocopheryl Acetate, Niacinamide, Calcium Pantothenate, Pyridoxine Hydrochloride, Thiamine Hydrochloride, Riboflavin, Betacarotene, Vitamin A Palmitate, Folic Acid, Vitamin D3, Vitamin K, Vitamin B12, BIotin), Choline Chloride, Taurine, L-carnitine, Anti-Forming Agent (900a).   Contains Milk and Soy.
Sizes: Size: Carton contains 6 x 1000mL soft packs.
Usage:
Check use by date on pouch.
Wash hands. Shake pouch well before use. Some separation of contents may occur.
Using clean technique, hold bag at base of SpikeRight® Plus port, remove port cap, and insert tip of threaded enteral spike set.
Turn threaded enteral spike set clockwise until tightly fastened.
Use at room temperature for up to 24 hours after spiking if proper technique is used.
Do not use if container is damaged, swollen or contents are coagulated.  Store unopened at room temperature.  Avoid excessive heat.  Do not freeze. Pouch is filled to deliver 1000ml. Actual fill volume is greater to compensate for residual volume remaining after pouch is drained.
